The Delta State Police Command said it has charged an ex-aide  of Gov. Ifeanyi Okowa, Friday Eluro, and two others to court. In a statement by the command’s acting public relations officer, ASP Chuks Oresewezie, the police said the suspects were charged at an Ashaka Magistrate Court on 18th February. Oresewezie said the suspects were arrested following a trending video of a woman that was stripped naked and tortured. The statement further alleged that the ex- aide “have more than 20 boys in his compound, whom he uses for his nefarious activities.” It added: “Friday Eluro and two others were charged of abduction, torture, and dehumanizing treatment of the victim”. The statement said the suspects have been remanded in Kwale prison.